cut -b3-
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch session list' command
# Terminal function that outputs comment-prefixed session list
#
# Default value: "cut -b3-"
#   Strips '# ' prefix from output lines (defensive pattern)
#   Function outputs all content as comments for safety
#   If interpreter misconfigured, output is just harmless comments
#
# Session list shows: PID, protocol, interface, state, config, started timestamp
#
# Example raw output (from function):
#   # VPN Sessions:
#   # PID        PROTOCOL     INTERFACE    STATE                CONFIG         STARTED
#   # 12345      wireguard    wg0          active/referenced    wg-US.conf     2025-10-05 22:00:00
#
# Example processed output (after cut -b3-):
#   VPN Sessions:
#   PID        PROTOCOL     INTERFACE    STATE                CONFIG         STARTED
#   12345      wireguard    wg0          active/referenced    wg-US.conf     2025-10-05 22:00:00
